A complex nested `@media` might result in a wrong CSS compilation.
Example Less file:
```
body{
    @media (max-width: 400px) {
        color:green;
    }
	h3{
		.before{
	        @media (max-width: 30px) {
	            color: red;
	        }
		}
	}
}
```
CSS output from lesscpy:
```
@media (max-width: 30px) {
    color: red;
}
@media (max-width: 400px) {
	body{
        color:green;
    }
}
```
Expected output:
```
@media (max-width: 400px) {
	body{
        color:green;
    }
}
@media (max-width: 30px) {
	body h3 .before{
    	color: red;
    }
}
```
The order of the generated `@media` is also strange...

*Removing the `h3` level completely solves the problem (the order is also fine)*

